==English==
===Proper noun===
'''Guy'''

# A male given name

===Noun===
'''guy''' ([[guys]])

# (''colloquial'') A male person
#:''A new '''guy''' started at the office today.''
# (''colloquial'') male and female persons
#:''Who are those guys?''
# (''colloquial'') a form of address for a group of male persons or a group of mixed male and female persons
#:''Hey guys!''
#(''colloquial'') A thing or object, usually used with a demonstrative adjective.
#:''Pass me that '''guy'''.''
#:''Out of all the computers made today, this '''guy''' is my favorite.''

